<!-- ============================= FAQ ============================= -->
<section class="faq-section" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">FAQ</div>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list">

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          Is decorative grass still allowed in Las Vegas?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>No. Nevada Assembly Bill 356 (AB356), signed in 2021, prohibits the installation of non-functional ornamental turf in the Las Vegas Valley by 2027. Existing grass must be removed. We specialize in beautiful, water-compliant alternatives including artificial turf, xeriscape, decomposed granite, and native desert plants — all of which look great and can be HOA-approved.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          Do I need HOA approval before starting?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>It depends on your neighborhood. Most planned communities in Summerlin, Henderson, and Green Valley require HOA approval for landscaping changes. We've worked with hundreds of Las Vegas HOAs and are familiar with their requirements. We can help you prepare your submittal package and guide you through the approval process at no extra charge.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          What's the best time of year to do landscaping in Las Vegas?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>Spring (March–May) and fall (September–November) are ideal. Desert plants establish better in moderate temperatures, hardscape materials are easier to work with, and crews can maintain quality without heat stress. That said, we work year-round — hardscaping, irrigation, and many other projects can be done safely in summer. We'll advise on the best timing for your specific project.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          How long does a typical landscaping project take?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>It varies by scope. A basic xeriscape or cleanup takes 1–3 days. A full front yard redesign typically runs 3–7 days. A complex backyard with a patio, pergola, fire pit, and lighting usually takes 2–4 weeks. We'll give you a detailed timeline during your free on-site consultation. We respect your time and keep you updated throughout the project.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          Are you licensed and insured in Nevada?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>Yes. We are fully licensed by the Nevada State Contractors Board, carry general liability insurance, and maintain workers' compensation coverage for all crew members. We're happy to provide proof of insurance and licensing before any work begins.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          Do you offer warranties on your work?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>Yes. We back all our installations with a workmanship warranty. Plants and natural materials also carry a 90-day establishment guarantee — if something doesn't take due to installation error, we'll replace it. Hardscape work (pavers, concrete, walls) carries a 1-year structural warranty. Manufacturer warranties on artificial turf and irrigation systems are passed through to you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          What areas of Las Vegas do you serve?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>We serve the entire Las Vegas Valley including: Las Vegas, Henderson, Summerlin, North Las Vegas, Green Valley, Boulder City, Enterprise, Paradise, Spring Valley, Whitney, Aliante, Centennial Hills, and surrounding communities. If you're unsure whether we cover your area, just call us at (702) 528-8324.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

